       cc [options] file -lcurses #include <curses.h>

       int curs_set(int visibility);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  function  sets  the appearance of the cursor based on
       the value of visibility: Invisible Terminal-specific  nor-
       mal mode Terminal-specific high visibility mode

       The  terminal  does  not necessarily support all the above
       values.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluuee
       If the terminal supports the cursor mode specified by vis-
       ibility,  then  returns the previous cursor state.  Other-
       wise, the function returns ERR.

EErrrroorrss
       No errors are defined.

